<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="45" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Widespread west of the Albertine rift into the area of the Central African Republic.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="45" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
At present only the holotype was known. The new material studied coming from the Natural History Museum of Budapest and the Africamuseum Tervuren considerably enlarges the known area of distribution of this species (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 111" captionStartId="F24" captionText="Figure 111. Distribution of species of the genus Poreuomena." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.68.60193.figure111" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/499203" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">111</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
